text: The excruciating never ending puzzle of who I am, who I was, & who I’m becoming being my main form of distraction. Searching for missing pieces that I lost time ago, disposing the pieces that I forcibly made fit, fixating on the pieces that don’t make any sense

author: ʕ•́ᴥ•̀ʔ
text: This past year can really be compared to being in jail. Mindlessly marking off days on the calendar as they go by, isolating myself in a small gray cell. The only view out of my bedroom window being the walls of an empty home

author: ʕ•́ᴥ•̀ʔ
text: Being alone to know myself more in depth without external interference, going inwards to help guide me on making authentic decisions - for myself and future

author: ʕ•́ᴥ•̀ʔ
text: If and when love does find me, I hope that this alone time that I’m taking will help me be the best partner I can be for the both of us — whoever they are, whenever they come

author: ʕ•́ᴥ•̀ʔ
text:
I love romance and fantasizing n whatnot, but I’m very glad to have not prioritized romance/dating/a significant other this year so far

author: ʕ•́ᴥ•̀ʔ
text:
